

# Real-World CDK CI/CD Pipeline Fl
In a real production setup**CDK itself is deployed via a pipeli**. Here's how it works end-to-en
# The Full Flow (Source → Build → Deploy Infrastructure → Deploy Ap

Developer pushes code to GitHub/CodeCommit
│
▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    CodePipeline                              │
│                                                              │
│  Stage 1: SOURCE                                             │
│  ├── Pull app code (Spring Boot Order Service)               │
│  └── Pull infra code (CDK project)                           │
│              │                                               │
│              ▼                                               │
│  Stage 2: BUILD (CodeBuild Project 1 — App Build)            │
│  ├── mvn clean package / gradle build                        │
│  ├── docker build -t order-service .                         │
│  ├── docker tag → ECR repo URL                               │
│  └── docker push → ECR                                       │
│              │                                               │
│              ▼                                               │
│  Stage 3: CDK SYNTH (CodeBuild Project 2 — Infra Build)      │
│  ├── cd cdk-infra                                            │
│  ├── npm install -g aws-cdk  (or use CDK in Gradle)          │
│  ├── cdk synth   ← generates CloudFormation templates        │
│  └── Output: cdk.out/ (CloudFormation JSON)                  │
│              │                                               │
│              ▼                                               │
│  Stage 4: CDK DEPLOY (CloudFormation Deploy)                 │
│  ├── Deploy NetworkStack (VPC)                               │
│  ├── Deploy OrderServiceStack (ECS + ALB + Fargate)          │
│  │     └── Fargate pulls NEW image from ECR                  │
│  └── ECS rolling update replaces old tasks with new ones     │
│              │                                               │
│              ▼                                               │
│  Stage 5 (optional): APPROVAL + PROD DEPLOY                 │
│  ├── Manual approval gate                                    │
│  └── Deploy to prod account/region                           │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


